git init --bare  #it is bare repo where can only pull or push the code(usualy used of creatiing the own central git server) where we need to set up the repository which act as git server 


for remote server on cloud there is no  root login setup over there to set this needs to following steps

1)vi   /etc/ssh/sshd_config
2) passwordauthentication yes, permuterootlogin yes --these two things needs to change
3)systemctl restart sshd


@to commit code we have to set global user name and password
git config --global user.name "sakib"
git config --global user.email "sakib@gmail.com"
git add .    *
this add files to stage where tracking of files are possible
git commit -m "messege"
git log
git log -p   //to show the commits with the changes
git remote add origin  url-of-remote


git push --set-upstream https://github.com/sak1122/Devops.git  developeme
nt //set new branch on remote and push the code

git branch   //to see the branchers
git branch -l
git branch -a  //all
git branch -r  //remote

git merge source destination
